The paper deals with predicting facial attributes from faces in the wild, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for this task, which is a popular machine learning technique. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also explores the use of mid-level CNN features for attribute prediction, which involves feature engineering and representation learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses datasets such as CelebA and LFWA, which are related to multimedia and image retrieval, respectively, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) possible sub-categories as well.
